1
00:00:00,191 --> 00:00:07,601
a cooperative family that won't object to travel, irregular hours, and other inconveniences which are part of selling,

2
00:00:07,791 --> 00:00:12,321
a family that will help the salesman over those inevitable rough spots.

3
00:00:13,311 --> 00:00:32,321
Executives today realize that what happens on weekends and between 6 p.m. and 9 a.m. directly affects a person's performance from 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. The person with a constructive off-the-job life nearly always is more successful than the person who lives in a dull,

4
00:00:32,351 --> 00:00:34,240
dreary home situation.

5
00:00:34,911 --> 00:00:41,121
Let's look in on the traditional way two co-workers, John and Milton, spend their weekends.

6
00:00:41,311 --> 00:00:44,401
Let's look, too, at the ultimate results.

7
00:00:45,391 --> 00:00:49,681
John's psychological diet on weekends is something like this.

8
00:00:49,950 --> 00:00:54,960
Usually, one evening is spent with some carefully selected, interesting friends.

9
00:00:55,230 --> 00:01:02,801
Another evening is generally spent out, perhaps at a movie, a civic or community project, or some friend's house.

10
00:01:03,470 --> 00:01:06,720
John devotes Saturday morning to Boy Scout work.

11
00:01:06,831 --> 00:01:10,561
Saturday afternoon he does errands and chores around the house.

12
00:01:10,751 --> 00:01:13,441
Often he works on some special project.

13
00:01:13,631 --> 00:01:16,881
Currently it's building a patio in the backyard.

14
00:01:17,151 --> 00:01:20,561
On Sundays, John and his family do something special.

15
00:01:20,831 --> 00:01:23,681
One Sunday, recently, they climbed a mountain.

16
00:01:23,791 --> 00:01:26,321
Another Sunday, they visited a museum.

17
00:01:26,591 --> 00:01:34,401
Occasionally, they drive into the nearby countryside, for John wants to buy some country property in the not-too-distant future.

18
00:01:34,991 --> 00:01:37,200
Sunday evening is spent quietly.

19
00:01:37,311 --> 00:01:41,041
John usually reads a book and catches up on the news.

20
00:01:41,551 --> 00:01:44,561
Wrapped up, John's weekends are planned.

21
00:01:44,751 --> 00:01:48,480
His many refreshing activities keep boredom locked out.

22
00:01:48,671 --> 00:01:52,000
John gets plenty of psychological sunshine.

23
00:01:52,671 --> 00:01:57,520
Milton's psychological diet is much less well balanced than John's.

24
00:01:57,551 --> 00:01:59,681
His weekends are unplanned.

25
00:01:59,871 --> 00:02:06,161
Milton is usually pretty tired on Friday night, but he goes through the motions of asking his wife,

26
00:02:06,351 --> 00:02:08,161
want to do anything tonight?

27
00:02:08,271 --> 00:02:10,161
But the plan dies there.

28
00:02:10,591 --> 00:02:15,601
Rarely do Milton and his wife entertain, and rarely are they invited out.

29
00:02:15,791 --> 00:02:22,401
Milton sleeps late on Saturday morning, and the rest of the day is taken up with chores of one kind or another.

30
00:02:22,751 --> 00:02:27,681
Saturday night, Milton and his family usually go to a movie or watch TV.

31
00:02:27,871 --> 00:02:29,441
What else is there to do?

32
00:02:29,791 --> 00:02:32,641
Milton spends most of Sunday morning in bed.

33
00:02:32,831 --> 00:02:38,561
Sunday afternoon, they drive over to Bill and Mary's, or Bill and Mary drive over to see them.

34
00:02:38,751 --> 00:02:43,121
Bill and Mary are the only couple Milton and his wife visit regularly.

35
00:02:43,551 --> 00:02:46,960
Milton's entire weekend is marked by boredom.

36
00:02:47,151 --> 00:02:54,321
By the time Sunday evening rolls around, the whole family is on each other's nerves as a result of cabin fever.

37
00:02:54,511 --> 00:03:00,480
There are no knock-down, drag-out fights, but there are hours of psychological warfare.

38
00:03:00,831 --> 00:03:04,321
Milton's weekend is dull, dreary, boring.

39
00:03:04,511 --> 00:03:07,681
Milton gets no psychological sunshine.
